Movie: Rebel Moon - Part One: A Child of Fire
Review: The more unsaid the better. Contender for worst movie of all time relative to its budget. Tedious, such a slog, and took two sit downs to finish despite its relatively modest runtime in todays cinema economy (only 134 mins; ya know the 3+ hour cut Snyder has would probably qualify as torture in some countries).
The final image of a battered, bruised and buried franchise is - fittingly - someone eating a cockroach and enjoying it.  Look at what these studios produce and how we consume them. Disgraceful.

took till the third act to hook me, but it did get there. A humbling movie…. making these things work all the way through is hard. And this is a real peaks and valleys movie: when it works it’s really good but when it fails it flops HARD
